<div class="allianceSection collapsable collapsed">
	 <h4 class="header">Fire Characteristics</h4>
	<div class="text"><i>Lepidium latifolium </i>regenerates rapidly from underground rootstalks and rhizomes following fires. Historically fire intensity and frequency in these wetlands varied with prevalence of drought cycles, lightning strikes, burning by Native Americans, and fires in surrounding uplands (Zouhar 2004c). However, <i>L. latifolium </i>is difficult to ignite and does not easily sustain burns because it lacks adequate fuels (Kilbride et al. 1997).</div>
